00:00:58.958 --> 00:01:01.527 line:0%
Um, first up,

00:01:01.560 --> 00:01:03.729 line:0%
a man who loves
the great outdoors

00:01:03.762 --> 00:01:06.399 line:0%
almost as much as he loves
helping those in need.

00:01:06.432 --> 00:01:08.601 line:0%
Which is a lot,
if that wasn't clear.

00:01:08.634 --> 00:01:11.070 line:0%
A man is traveling across
the country to spread goodwill,

00:01:11.103 --> 00:01:13.339 line:0%
and his only tool
is a lawn mower.

00:01:13.372 --> 00:01:16.075 line:0%
<i> Rodney Smith Jr.'s known
 as Lawnmower Man.</i>

00:01:16.108 --> 00:01:18.411 line:0%
<i> He says the idea came
 from a chance encounter</i>

00:01:18.444 --> 00:01:20.346 line:0%
<i> he had one day
 with an elderly man.</i>

00:01:20.379 --> 00:01:22.148 line:0%
He looked like he was
struggling, so I pulled over

00:01:22.181 --> 00:01:23.983 line:0%
and helped him out.
That night, I decided

00:01:24.016 --> 00:01:25.785 line:0%
to mow free lawns
for the elderly,

00:01:25.818 --> 00:01:27.386 line:0%
disabled, single mothers,
and veterans.

00:01:27.419 --> 00:01:29.322
McBROOM:<i> Smith says
 he'll travel to all 50 states</i>

00:01:29.355 --> 00:01:31.224
<i> to mow laws for those in need.</i>

00:01:31.257 --> 00:01:33.292
Wow, inspiring story,

00:01:33.325 --> 00:01:35.561
mowing lawns for the needy
in all 50 states.

00:01:35.594 --> 00:01:37.063
Your neighbors must love you.

00:01:37.096 --> 00:01:39.599
Heck, the whole country
is gonna be your neighbor soon.

00:01:39.632 --> 00:01:41.868
Everyone's friend,
that's you, Rodney.

00:01:41.901 --> 00:01:44.303
Everybody loves Rodney.

00:01:44.336 --> 00:01:47.874
Rodney, must feel pretty good
about yourself.

00:01:47.907 --> 00:01:51.711
Pretty... good.

00:01:51.744 --> 00:01:53.913
Hey, Rodney...

00:01:53.946 --> 00:01:55.948
You think you're better than me?

00:01:55.981 --> 00:01:57.950
Is that what you think, Rodney?

00:01:57.983 --> 00:01:59.852
I can mow lawns
in all 50 states.

00:01:59.885 --> 00:02:01.621
I'm handy, I'm good with tools.

00:02:01.654 --> 00:02:03.055
I built a birdhouse
in fifth grade,

00:02:03.088 --> 00:02:05.491
a good one,
the bird is still in it.

00:02:05.524 --> 00:02:07.360
I can buy a lawn mower.

00:02:07.393 --> 00:02:09.195
I can definitely buy one,
and find one,

00:02:09.228 --> 00:02:10.796
and identify one
in a hardware store,

00:02:10.829 --> 00:02:12.632
then I can buy it
in a heartbeat.

00:02:12.665 --> 00:02:14.700
How much could it be?
I don't know.

00:02:14.733 --> 00:02:17.937
$30,000, probably, could be.

00:02:17.970 --> 00:02:20.339
Plus, I can go to any state
I want,

00:02:20.372 --> 00:02:23.042
as long as it's not both Dakotas
or one of the Virginias.

00:02:23.075 --> 00:02:24.377
They know what they did.

00:02:24.410 --> 00:02:25.611
Screw you, Rodney.

00:02:25.644 --> 00:02:27.580
You're not better than me.

00:02:27.613 --> 00:02:31.217
This next story is sure
to make you smile.

00:02:31.250 --> 00:02:33.252
And maybe also a bit hungry.

00:02:33.285 --> 00:02:34.921
A fast food worker in
Chesterfield County

00:02:34.954 --> 00:02:38.925
is receiving a lot of praise
after this video went viral.

00:02:38.958 --> 00:02:41.661
You can see him--
Run, Forrest, run--

00:02:41.694 --> 00:02:44.230
chasing down a customer who
forgot part of her order.

00:02:44.263 --> 00:02:45.898
The dedicated worker
successfully got

00:02:45.931 --> 00:02:47.900
the customer's second bag
of food to her

00:02:47.933 --> 00:02:51.504
before jogging back and looking
just a little bit tired.

00:02:51.537 --> 00:02:53.005
Oh, well,
you can't argue with that.

00:02:53.038 --> 00:02:54.707
That's just a nice thing to do.

00:02:54.740 --> 00:02:57.143
Glad a nice guy like that
in the middle of the country

00:02:57.176 --> 00:02:59.078
is getting that kind
of attention.

00:02:59.111 --> 00:03:00.980
He's probably feeling pretty
good about--

00:03:01.013 --> 00:03:03.115
You think you're better than me?

00:03:03.148 --> 00:03:05.585
That's not a run,
that's a shuffle at best.

00:03:05.618 --> 00:03:07.186
I've sprinted out
of Chick-fil-As

00:03:07.219 --> 00:03:09.689
twice as fast as that,
carrying way more bags

00:03:09.722 --> 00:03:11.924
of morally-dubious
fried chicken.

00:03:11.957 --> 00:03:13.626
And how dare you abandon
your post?

00:03:13.659 --> 00:03:16.195
It's chaos back at that
Chick-fil-A with you gone.

00:03:16.228 --> 00:03:18.364
They're serving burritos
and grilling pad Thai,

00:03:18.397 --> 00:03:20.366
and not weighing in on what
constitutes love anymore.

00:03:20.399 --> 00:03:21.734
You're a monster.

00:03:21.767 --> 00:03:24.203
How on Earth can you think
you're better than me?

00:03:24.236 --> 00:03:26.272
Up next...

00:03:26.305 --> 00:03:28.374
Have you got a heart ticking in
your chest?

00:03:28.407 --> 00:03:30.743
Careful, this story
is sure to melt it.

00:03:30.776 --> 00:03:32.712
Superdaddy saved the big show.

00:03:32.745 --> 00:03:33.946
Take a look.

00:03:33.979 --> 00:03:35.381
Little Bella, hysterical,

00:03:35.414 --> 00:03:38.117
crying on stage during her
annual ballet recital.

00:03:38.150 --> 00:03:39.986
Dad appears from the wings
to try to calm her down.

00:03:40.019 --> 00:03:41.454
MALE TV REPORTER:
Ah, with the baby.

00:03:41.487 --> 00:03:43.022
FEMALE TV REPORTER:
While holding a baby,

00:03:43.055 --> 00:03:44.657
-Yeah.
-he joined the ballet line.

00:03:44.690 --> 00:03:46.559
Look at the plié.

00:03:46.592 --> 00:03:48.728
He's like,
"I got this. I'm Superdad."

00:03:48.761 --> 00:03:50.696
(bleep) you, Superdad!

00:03:50.729 --> 00:03:52.331
You think you're better than me?

00:03:52.364 --> 00:03:54.267
You think you're such
a great dad

00:03:54.300 --> 00:03:57.236
because your amazing moment
of superdad-ness went viral

00:03:57.269 --> 00:03:59.605
and your kids will love you
forever and ever?

00:03:59.638 --> 00:04:01.374
You think I can't go viral?

00:04:01.407 --> 00:04:03.209
You think I can't dance
with a baby?

00:04:03.242 --> 00:04:05.745
Someone give me a baby.

00:04:05.778 --> 00:04:09.081
Yes. There we go.

00:04:09.114 --> 00:04:11.584
(cheering and applause)

00:04:11.617 --> 00:04:13.452
